Hey Stephen - thanks for putting that request in however, I'm not having much luck getting the system to accept my new password, so whenever you get a second, could you please ask them to reset my account?

In the meantime, the web developer didn't carry across your Google Tag Manager container code which means that all the tracking for Google Ads is inactive and likely has been since you switched to the new website. Could you please ask them to install the following code:

1. Paste this code as high in the <head> of the page as possible:
<!-- Google Tag Manager -->
<script>(function(w,d,s,l,i){w[l]=w[l]||[];w[l].push({'gtm.start':
new Date().getTime(),event:'gtm.js'});var f=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],
j=d.createElement(s),dl=l!='dataLayer'?'&l='+l:'';j.async=true;j.src=
'https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtm.js?id='+i+dl;f.parentNode.insertBefore(j,f);
})(window,document,'script','dataLayer','GTM-NHRMSMN4');</script>
<!-- End Google Tag Manager -->

2. Paste this code immediately after the opening <body> tag:
<!-- Google Tag Manager (noscript) -->
<noscript><iframe src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/ns.html?id=GTM-NHRMSMN4"
height="0" width="0" style="display:none;visibility:hidden"></iframe></noscript>
<!-- End Google Tag Manager (noscript) -->

Thanks,
Jes
